title: For Sale/Trade:  WATCH OUT FOR TRAJETECH AMMO!!!!!!!!!!!
postcontent: Please please please watch out for Trajetech ammo.  I know MANY people that have been having issues with them. Many getting stuck in chamber, I've had a couple guys have squibs stuck halfway down there barrel and one of them DID load a round behind the other one.  Luckily he was smart enough to check his barrel because it just didn't "feel right."  I get it, times are hard and you have to take what you can get but just be careful.  If it doesn't feel right, stop.  If it doesn't extract, stop.  Check your barrel.  DO NOT RACK THE SLIDE AND PULL THE TRIGGER without checking the barrel.  I talked to a few guys I know and apparently they are having some employee issues and they're not loading like they used to.  QC apparently has gone down.  I guess they were loading .380's in 9mm boxes.  Take it at face value just PLEASE BE CAREFUL!

postcontent:
Stop paying outrageous prices for ammo, and I'll bet it will start to reappear.  Many of these jerks are going every morning and buying up what little ammo is coming in so that they can turn around and flip it for a profit.  I say we take away their incentive by not paying $90 for a brick of .22lr, $30 for a box of 9mm, etc.

When you notice someone selling 3, and only 3, boxes of a particular ammo that is often sold at walmart, use your brain and think, I bet that guy went, bought his limit on that ammo, and is now ripping people off.  Then don't buy from him.  Or do, I don't care.  But I won't.

postcontent:
Teaches the basic knowledge, skills, and attitude for safely owning and operating a concealed carried handgun.

Provides students with specialized instruction geared towards obtaining a concealed carry permit focusing on firearm safety, responsibility of the concealed carrier, laws and statutes, implications of usage, holsters, clothing and concealment, drawing and firing from concealed positions. title: For Sale/Trade:  REDUCED: Glock 21 Extended Mags
postcontent:
Selling a lot of 5 Glock 21 magazines, 26 round capacity. 

Now for the disclaimers. I have no idea who made these. Got them in a package deal before the Newtown incident. Comparing photos from online distributors has convinced me that they are not KCI. The round counters are evenly spaced, unlike the factory Glock 21 mags. They each hold 26 rounds, so the floor plate isn't really an extension like you see on the others. 

I've checked multiple distributors and auction sites. I have yet to find magazines like this. So why sell them? I only have one Glock 21 pistol, and these things are not practical for CCW at all. I haven't personally tested these other than loading them to full capacity, which they do just fine. 

Asking price is $30 each, $150 for the lot. Email or text: REDACTED

Will not ship to states where banned.

I am willing to trade for reloading dies, powder, bullets, and other related supplies.

title: For Sale:  Exotic Shotgun Ammo!!!!!! For 410, 20 and 12 Guage! dragons breath!
postcontent:
Below is a list of exotic shotgun ammo for sale, this ammo has been manufactured by an ffl liscensed company. The ammo is made to exacting tolerances and can be used for joy or to defend your family. 

Enjoy. my phone number is 918 six one nine 3772. please text if you have any questions at all.

i do ship, preferably orders over a 100$, remember the incendiary or tracer ammo requires a hasmat fee to ship. in the past it has been a 27 dollar fee.


please email if you have any questions
i prefer to meet on the south side of tulsa near jenks.
we pay our taxes and tax has been included.

sales cannot be shipped unless in very large amounts
***12 Guage***
*Rubber Ball less-than-leathal 2 for $10- High density rubber ball that at close range is capable of bruising, but at 40 feet is like getting hit with a paint ball.

*Ball and Chain 2 for $12- 2 Steel balls held together with a 4 1/2" braided steel chain. It will leave a 5 1/2" wound cavity.

*3" Magnum 3 Ball and Chain 2 for $14- 3 Steel balls held together with 2 braided steel chains. It will leave a 9" wound cavity.

*Incindiary Slugs 2 for $14- This round when shot at a hard, stable surface will flash ignite. This round turns your 12 guage into a mini granade launcher.

*Johnson Door Breaching Rounds 2 for $12- This round is a large ceramic slug, that when shot at very close range to a door knob or hinge, will dislodge the knob and then turn into shards of less lethal fragmentation

*Discarding Sabot Rounds 2 for $12- This round is metal piercing. It contains 2 different types of metal. Then the first metal hits a plate of steel, it softens it. Then the 2nd type of metal is able to fly through! google m1 abrahms round to see the technology/

*Steel Slug 2 for $12- A 2" steel slug capable of going through 5/8" thick sheet metal.

*FireBall 2 for $14- A 150 Foot Ball of Fire and Sparkles. This round looks like the biggest, hottest roman candle you have ever seen!

*Super Rhodesian 2 for $13-High density steel buck shot and bird shot.

*Flechettes 2 for $14- 1 1/2" steel darts that fly at 1,900 FTS but the round has no recoil.
this is our meanest round, the darts sail through a inch and a half piece of pine. my favorite by far.

*Buck and Slug 2 for $14- Also called a bear round, Buck and Slug is a 2 oz steel slug with steel buck shot behind it.


*Attack Pack $35- Contains 2 rounds of Ball and Chain, 2 rounds of Flechettes and 2 rounds of Johnson Door Breeching.

*Attack Pack $39- Contains 2 rounds of Ball and Chain, 2 rounds of Flechettes and 2 rounds of Super Rhodesian.

title: For Sale:  20 cans of bulk 5.45x39
postcontent: I have 20 cans of surplus Soviet/Bulgarian that I would like to sell. (1080 rounds per can) It is really nice ammo, accurate and powerful. I shoot it through my Huldra and AK74 and it works great. It is corrosive. It won't matter in the Huldra, but clean with Windex (with ammonia) after shooting in other rifles, cleans up quick. I want to sell it in bulk. If you just want a can or two, Fleet Farm has it for $220/can. I want to sell a minimum of 5 cans, at $210 per can, so without the tax it will save you $100. 10 cans for $200/can, 20 cans @ $190/can. It is hard to find on internet and going for at least $250/can. I'd prefer to meet in Green Bay area, but will travel reasonable distance in WI or UP. Prefer not to ship. Please include text/phone # with reply.

title: For Sale:  USGI M1 Carbine: Rockola
postcontent:
Selling an USGI Rockola M1 Carbine. If you have never shot one, you are missing a great experience and piece of our military history. It is an original USGI with no import marks and came from CMP a few years back. It has Austrian markings on the trigger housing to add to its history (See more at http://www.bavarianm1carbines.com/index.html). 

It has a mid 4 million series serial number. Stock is dark walnut with the usual nicks and dents for a rifle that has been to war and back.

I am selling it with two 30-rd magazines and one 15-round magazine (USGI Rockola). It also has the sling and oiler. 

Will also make available to buyer additional 15- and 30-round magazines and several boxes of carbine ammo at very reasonable prices if desired.

If you are not familar with the M1 Carbine, these are our first real a$$ault rifle. My favorite gun to shoot. With the fast approaching personal transfer background requirement and high-capacity magazine ban, I decided it is time get rid of the extras.

Please send me a message if you have questions. Not interested in trades and must be FTF.

Thanks for looking

title: For Sale:  Remington 700 SPS
postcontent:
I have a mint condition, Remington 700 SPS in .223... I bought this about 3 months ago, and spent a ton of money on a scope, base, rings, Choate sniper stock, bipod, etc.. Just 45 rounds down the barrel. patched after every 2 rounds. My eyes have gotten to the point that precision shooting is something I USED to do well. My son can shoot sub MOA with it.

It has the beavertail vented, OD Green stock and the Exmark trigger. Not a scratch on this gun. I'm taking the Choate stock, Leupold MK4 M1 scope, Warne base, TRS steel rings, and the bipod off to make it more affordable.

$550.00 is the price I gave, and what I want back. If you'd like to talk about the extra stuff, that's an option. I can, and will sell the whole rig. A phone call is best for that instead of endless emailing about it. I do not have a picture, so I borrowed one from the internet. My gun is EXACTLY like this, with the Green stock.
